snippet.textDisplay: R.E. 3 was my first Resident Evil game and my favorite. Years and years later I played the original and 2 on the PSP and liked them. I also played 0 on the gamecube that I thought was okay. I read the Code Veronica comics and saw the first 3 R.E. films (and I stopped at 3 because it was retarded) and saw the animated film, Degeneration. R.E. 4 I never got into and I have no desire to play any others. R.E. 3 to me is the one I will always play and it brings back great memories of terror, fear, and sweat. It'll be good to see my boy remastered and now he has a flamethrower.
snippet.textOriginal: R.E. 3 was my first Resident Evil game and my favorite. Years and years later I played the original and 2 on the PSP and liked them. I also played 0 on the gamecube that I thought was okay. I read the Code Veronica comics and saw the first 3 R.E. films (and I stopped at 3 because it was retarded) and saw the animated film, Degeneration. R.E. 4 I never got into and I have no desire to play any others. R.E. 3 to me is the one I will always play and it brings back great memories of terror, fear, and sweat.
